{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trCommemoration|text', 'text' : 'Second Sunday of Lent. St. Gregory Palamas, Archbishop of Thessaloniki'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trShortCommemoration1|text', 'text' : 'Second Sunday of Lent - St. Gregory Palamas'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trInsert1', 'text' : 'our father among the saints Gregory Palamas, Archbishop of Thessaloniki,'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trInsert2', 'text' : 'whose memory we celebrate,'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trNote|text', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trHO|daytitle', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trHO|commemorations', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trHO|description1', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trHO|description2', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trHO|note1', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trHO|note2', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trDismissal', 'text' : 'He who rose from the dead,'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trVE|Stichera01|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 2.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trVE|Stichera01|melody', 'text' : 'Are there any worthy crowns.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trVE|Stichera01|text', 'text' : 'Are there any worthy songs of praise so that we might sing them to the Hierarch? For he is the trumpet of theology, and he is the fire-breathing mouth of grace, the distinguished vessel of the Spirit; the pillar of the Church, indeed unshakable; the great joy and exultation of the universe; the flowing river of wisdom, and the lamp of divine light, the resplendently shining star that illumines creation brilliantly.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trVE|Stichera02|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 2.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trVE|Stichera02|melody', 'text' : 'Are there any worthy crowns.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trVE|Stichera02|text', 'text' : 'Are there any hymns like flowers in bloom, for a wreath to crown the holy Hierarch? He is a defender of Orthodoxy, and the adversary of heresy, and the Faith's most earnest protector; the great guide, leader and teacher of divine wisdom; the sacred and all-harmonious harp the Spirit played; the golden tongue, and the fountain, which is ever gushing forth to the faithful streams of cures; the great and truly admirable Gregory.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trVE|Stichera03|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 2.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trVE|Stichera03|melody', 'text' : 'Are there any worthy crowns.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trVE|Stichera03|text', 'text' : 'Are there any lips of earthborn men that can worthily extol the Hierarch? For he is the teacher of all the Church, and he is the preacher of the light of God; and the Holy Trinity's true mystic; the great pride of the monastics and their ornament, who shined forth in contemplation and the active life; Thessaloniki's great glory, and a fellow-citizen now in heaven of that divine, stupendous gusher of fragant oil, Demetrius.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trVE|SticGlory|mode', 'text' : 'Mode pl. 2.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trVE|SticGlory|melody', 'text' : 'Idiomelon.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trVE|SticGlory|text', 'text' : 'O devout, thrice-blessed, all-holy Father, good Shepherd, and Disciple of Christ the Chief Shepherd, you laid down your life for the sheep. O our God-bearing Father, Gregory, pray for us, that by your intercessions the Lord grant us His great mercy.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trVE|AposGlory|mode', 'text' : 'Mode pl. 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trVE|AposGlory|melody', 'text' : 'Idiomelon.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trVE|AposGlory|text', 'text' : 'Your tongue, watchful in teaching, rings in the ears of our hearts and awakens the souls of the slothful. Your words, inspired by God, are a ladder leading us from earth to heaven. O Gregory, the marvel of Thessaly, pray to Christ without ceasing, that we who honor you may be illumined with the divine light.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trVE|AposTheotokion|mode', 'text' : 'Mode pl. 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trVE|AposTheotokion|melody', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trVE|AposTheotokion|text', 'text' : 'O Virgin who did not know man and yet ineffably conceived God in the flesh, Mother of the Most High God, accept entreaties from your supplicants, All-blameless one. To all you grant purification of their offenses. We pray you now accept our supplications, and entreat Him, to save us all.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trVE|Apolytikion1|mode', 'text' : 'Mode pl. 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trVE|Apolytikion1|melody', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trVE|Apolytikion1|text', 'text' : 'Beacon of Orthodox belief, the strong support of the Church and her teacher inspired by God, you are the ornament of monks, the unassailable champion of theologians, O Gregory the Wonder-worker and the boast of Thessalonica, the messenger of grace. Forever earnestly entreat for the salvation of our souls.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trVE|ApolTheotokion|mode', 'text' : 'Mode pl. 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trVE|ApolTheotokion|melody', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trVE|ApolTheotokion|text', 'text' : 'Born of a Virgin, O Good One who also endured crucifixion for our sake, who by death took the spoils of death as plunder and showed resurrection, being God, O despise not the ones that You formed with Your own hand. Demonstrate Your love for man, O Lord of mercy, and accept Your Mother, the Theotokos, who intercedes on our behalf, O Savior, and save us a despairing people.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|PostGospelGlory|mode', 'text' : 'Mode pl. 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|PostGospelGlory|melody', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|PostGospelGlory|text', 'text' : 'Open to me the gates of repentance, O Giver of Life, for early in the morning my spirit hastens to Your holy temple, bringing the temple of my body all defiled. But as one compassionate, cleanse me, I pray, by Your loving-kindness and mercy.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|PostGospelBoth|mode', 'text' : 'Mode pl. 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|PostGospelBoth|melody', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|PostGospelBoth|text', 'text' : 'Guide me in the paths of salvation, O Theotokos, for I have befouled my soul with shameful sins and I heedlessly squandered all of my life's resources. By your intercession deliver me from every uncleanness.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|PostGospelIdiomelon|mode', 'text' : 'Mode pl. 2.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|PostGospelIdiomelon|melody', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|PostGospelIdiomelon|text', 'text' : 'When I ponder in my wretchedness on the many terrible things that I have done, I tremble for that fearful day, the Day of Judgment. But trusting in the mercy of Your compassion, like David I cry to You, "Have mercy on me, O God, according to Your great mercy."'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|C1|title', 'text' : 'Canon for the Saint.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|C1|verse', 'text' : 'Saint of God, intercede for us.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode1C11|ode', 'text' : 'Ode i.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode1C11|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode1C11|melody', 'text' : 'I open my mouth.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode1C11|text', 'text' : 'O God-inspired orators, with the select theologians, come * together with every tongue that speaks the things of God, * join in unison to worthily sing praises * to the Spirit's orator, the holy Gregory.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode1C12|ode', 'text' : 'Ode i.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode1C12|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode1C12|melody', 'text' : 'I open my mouth.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode1C12|text', 'text' : 'The best of all shepherds of Thessaloniki, and pillar of * the Faith, and the champion of the Church be praised by me. * For he is the true adornment of the order * of bishops, Saint Gregory, great and magnificent.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode1C13|ode', 'text' : 'Ode i.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode1C13|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode1C13|melody', 'text' : 'I open my mouth.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode1C13|text', 'text' : 'From earliest childhood, father, you longed for the higher life. * From youth you submitted to a perfect frame of mind. * And you proved to be alike in mind and manner * with him whose namesake you are, O divine Gregory.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode1C1T|ode', 'text' : 'Ode i.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode1C1T|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode1C1T|melody', 'text' : 'I open my mouth.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode1C1T|text', 'text' : 'All-blameless one, be to me a path of life, ever guiding me * unto the divine abodes. For I have wandered astray * and am sliding down * into the pit of evils. * From this, through your intercessions, lead me up again.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode3C11|ode', 'text' : 'Ode iii.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode3C11|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode3C11|melody', 'text' : 'Establish your servants.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode3C11|text', 'text' : 'Adhering faithfully to the courses * of your godly teachings, we escape * the wiles of the heretics. * And through your sacred treatises * we put to flight all their arrays, O most divine father Gregory.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode3C12|ode', 'text' : 'Ode iii.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode3C12|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode3C12|melody', 'text' : 'Establish your servants.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode3C12|text', 'text' : 'Possessing the hypostatic wisdom * of God in your heart, you put an end * unto the foolish sophistries * of heretics, O blessed one, * and thus did you obliterate their unsound snortings resoundingly.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode3C13|ode', 'text' : 'Ode iii.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode3C13|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode3C13|melody', 'text' : 'Establish your servants.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode3C13|text', 'text' : 'You mortified all impassioned pleasures, * O wise one, of the corrupted flesh, * and vivified ascetically * the natural movements of your soul * which proved to be an instrument, O blessed Saint, of theology.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode3C1T|ode', 'text' : 'Ode iii.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode3C1T|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode3C1T|melody', 'text' : 'Establish your servants.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode3C1T|text', 'text' : 'With full knowledge and by my own free choice, * I eagerly loved a way of life * both prodigal and full of shame. * But bind me to the tender love * of God, O Virgin Bride of God, through your divine intercessory prayers.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode3Kathisma1|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode3Kathisma1|melody', 'text' : 'Come quickly.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode3Kathisma1|text', 'text' : 'O wise one, the error of the heretics you consumed * and properly clarified for all the Orthodox Faith * and brought light to all the world. * Hence you were manifested as a champion and victor, * one of the Church's pillars, and a genuine bishop. * Cease not interceding with Christ that all of us might be saved.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode3Kathisma2|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode3Kathisma2|melody', 'text' : 'Come quickly.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode3Kathisma2|text', 'text' : 'Be swift to accept our fervent prayers, O Lady and Queen, * and take them, all-blameless Maiden, and present them for us * before your own Son and God. * Obliterate the scandals of the slanderous babblers, * frustrate the machinations and humble the boldness * of the godless, O Pure one, who against your servants have taken arms.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode4C11|ode', 'text' : 'Ode iv.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode4C11|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode4C11|melody', 'text' : 'When the Prophet Habakkuk.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode4C11|text', 'text' : 'Opening your mouth, O wise father, you preached * the wisdom of God which you constantly * carefully studied in your heart, O blessed Saint, * and proved the foolish Barlaam * lacking understanding and frivolous.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode4C12|ode', 'text' : 'Ode iv.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode4C12|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode4C12|melody', 'text' : 'When the Prophet Habakkuk.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode4C12|text', 'text' : 'You have sunk beneath the earth, for you submit * to the laws of nature, O sweetest Saint. * But in the morning you shall rise again with Christ, * O sun that knows no eventide, * watching over all as you intercede.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode4C13|ode', 'text' : 'Ode iv.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode4C13|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode4C13|melody', 'text' : 'When the Prophet Habakkuk.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode4C13|text', 'text' : 'Blessed one, God's grace has exhibited you * as a watchful guardian of the flock, * as a good shepherd and a second Gregory * the Theologian, as the boast * and the great support of the Orthodox.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode4C1T|ode', 'text' : 'Ode iv.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode4C1T|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode4C1T|melody', 'text' : 'When the Prophet Habakkuk.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode4C1T|text', 'text' : 'I beseech you, open the ears of my soul, * O Mother of God who gave birth unto the Lord who opened once the ears of the deaf. * And thus enable me to hear * and fulfill the utterances of God.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode5C11|ode', 'text' : 'Ode v.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode5C11|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode5C11|melody', 'text' : 'Amazed was the universe.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode5C11|text', 'text' : 'O hierarch Gregory, using the sickle of your words * and your sacred writings, you have cut down * the thorny heresies and the spurious shoots * of scandalous teachings as if weeds, * and you sowed the pious seeds of the Faith of the Orthodox.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode5C12|ode', 'text' : 'Ode v.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode5C12|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode5C12|melody', 'text' : 'Amazed was the universe.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode5C12|text', 'text' : 'Your words and your eminent writings are unto those who read * honey from the rock and dew from heaven, * the bread of angels, nectar, ambrosia, * living water's well, sugar and spice, * holy father Gregory, who are most wise in everything.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode5C13|ode', 'text' : 'Ode v.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode5C13|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode5C13|melody', 'text' : 'Amazed was the universe.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode5C13|text', 'text' : 'As their common teacher do the earth and sea acknowledge you, * and as Orthodoxy's sacred pillar, * and of divine dogmas the august armory, * the wise theologian of the Church, * comrade and companion of the Apostles alike in all.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode5C1T|ode', 'text' : 'Ode v.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode5C1T|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode5C1T|melody', 'text' : 'Amazed was the universe.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode5C1T|text', 'text' : 'Immaculate Virgin, wash away the squalor of my heart * with the flowing waters of compunction, * and also grant unto me the ways to repent * through your holy prayers unto God * who is most compassionate and whom you bore ineffably.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode6C11|ode', 'text' : 'Ode vi.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode6C11|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode6C11|melody', 'text' : 'O godly-minded believers.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode6C11|text', 'text' : 'The tongue and impious insolence * of witless Barlaam have been shattered by the dogmas and the words * and the acute understanding of the Emperor with wisdom and you, O Gregory.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode6C12|ode', 'text' : 'Ode vi.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode6C12|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode6C12|melody', 'text' : 'O godly-minded believers.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode6C12|text', 'text' : 'Let us with hymns honor the divine * harp of the Holy Spirit, the trumpet that distinctly has proclaimed * the sacred mysteries of the Lord, * Thessaloniki's prelate, the tongue that spoke of God.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode6C13|ode', 'text' : 'Ode vi.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode6C13|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode6C13|melody', 'text' : 'O godly-minded believers.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode6C13|text', 'text' : 'O fiery pillar, like that of old * which went before the people, you burned up the enemies of the Faith, * while you enlightened the body of Believers, father Gregory, godly-minded one.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode6C1T|ode', 'text' : 'Ode vi.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode6C1T|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode6C1T|melody', 'text' : 'O godly-minded believers.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode6C1T|text', 'text' : 'O all-pure Lady, become for me * serenity, a harbor of consolation bearing me across * to a divine waveless anchorage, * and thus appease my passions' violently surging storm.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Kontakion1|mode', 'text' : 'Mode pl. 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Kontakion1|melody', 'text' : 'O Champion General.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Kontakion1|text', 'text' : 'With one accord, we sing your praises, Father Gregory * who speaks from God, sonorous trumpet of theology, * and divine and sacred organ of holy wisdom. * But as intellect that stands before the Intellect, * unto Him direct our intellect, so unto you * we may cry aloud: Rejoice, O herald of grace.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Oikos1|text', 'text' : 'As a herald of mysteries, you appeared on earth plainly, proclaiming things divine unto mortals. Endowed with a human mind and flesh, and yet speaking in the tongue of the bodiless, you amazed us and convinced us to cry out to you, O godly rhetor:'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Oikos12|text', 'text' : 'Rejoice, through whom the darkness was banished; Rejoice, through whom the light did supplant it.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Oikos13|text', 'text' : 'Rejoice, uncreated Divinity's messenger; Rejoice, the confuter of one created and nonsensical.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Oikos14|text', 'text' : 'Rejoice, you who called God's nature an inaccessible height; Rejoice, you who called His energy a depth difficult to sight.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Oikos15|text', 'text' : 'Rejoice, for you correctly have discoursed on God's glory; Rejoice, for you have spoken against the views of the wicked.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Oikos16|text', 'text' : 'Rejoice, O star that made the Sun evident; Rejoice, the bowl imparting the sweet nectar.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Oikos17|text', 'text' : 'Rejoice, through whom the truth shines refulgent; Rejoice, through whom was falsehood extinguished.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Oikos18|text', 'text' : 'Rejoice, O herald of grace.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Synaxarion|commemoration|text', 'text' : 'On this day, the second Sunday of Lent, we observe the memory of our Father among the Saints Gregory Palamas, Archbishop of Thessalonica.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Synaxarion|couplet1|title', 'text' : 'Verses'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Synaxarion|couplet1|verse1', 'text' : 'The mind truly great and the Light's bright herald'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Synaxarion|couplet1|verse2', 'text' : 'Is led by light's Source to radiance never-setting.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Synaxarion|narration1|p01|text', 'text' : '[paragraph 01]'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Synaxarion|narration1|p02|text', 'text' : '[paragraph 02]'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Synaxarion|narration1|p03|text', 'text' : '[paragraph 03]'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Synaxarion|narration1|p04|text', 'text' : '[paragraph 04]'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Synaxarion|narration1|p05|text', 'text' : '[paragraph 05]'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Synaxarion|narration1|p06|text', 'text' : '[paragraph 06]'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Synaxarion|narration1|p07|text', 'text' : '[paragraph 07]'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Synaxarion|narration2|p01|text', 'text' : '[paragraph 01]'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Synaxarion|narration2|p02|text', 'text' : '[paragraph 02]'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Synaxarion|narration2|p03|text', 'text' : '[paragraph 03]'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Synaxarion|narration2|p04|text', 'text' : '[paragraph 04]'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Synaxarion|narration2|p05|text', 'text' : '[paragraph 05]'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Synaxarion|narration2|p06|text', 'text' : '[paragraph 06]'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Synaxarion|narration2|p07|text', 'text' : '[paragraph 07]'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Synaxarion|lastline|text', 'text' : 'By his intercessions, O God, have mercy on us and save us. Amen.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode7C11|ode', 'text' : 'Ode vii.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode7C11|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode7C11|melody', 'text' : 'Godly-minded three.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode7C11|text', 'text' : 'All who study well * your discourses and writings are initiated into the sacred knowledge of God. * With spiritual wisdom are they filled, O Gregory. * They theologize about God's uncreated grace * and His energies and actions.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode7C12|ode', 'text' : 'Ode vii.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode7C12|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode7C12|melody', 'text' : 'Godly-minded three.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode7C12|text', 'text' : 'You completely crushed * the broadsword and the bows of those who taught fallacious beliefs. * And Barlaam's proud conceit * together with all the power of the heretics, holy hierarch, * you shattered, like a spider's web * by a massive rock is scattered.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode7C13|ode', 'text' : 'Ode vii.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode7C13|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode7C13|melody', 'text' : 'Godly-minded three.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode7C13|text', 'text' : 'By your discourses * and dogmas and your treatises was the Orthodox faith of pious Christians confirmed. * The boldness of heresy halted, O Gregory. * Confutation of the true Faith and the might of those * with fallacious views has ended.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode7C1T|ode', 'text' : 'Ode vii.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode7C1T|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode7C1T|melody', 'text' : 'Godly-minded three.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode7C1T|text', 'text' : 'By the sicknesses * of passions we are withered up. Yet we know you to be truly a fountain of cures. * Divine and salvific waters do we draw therefrom. * And we cry aloud: All-pure one, blessed is the fruit * of your womb, all-holy Virgin.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode8C11|ode', 'text' : 'Ode viii.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode8C11|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode8C11|melody', 'text' : 'Guiltless were those Servants.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode8C11|text', 'text' : 'Resembling the holy Theologians * in mind and in manner, now you stand before * the throne of the All-merciful * with them, O most wise Gregory, * the excellence of hierarchs. And now you worship God, * O Primate of Thessaloniki, * splendidly adorned in the hierarchal glory.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode8C12|ode', 'text' : 'Ode viii.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode8C12|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode8C12|melody', 'text' : 'Guiltless were those Servants.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode8C12|text', 'text' : 'God foreknew your purity of reason * before you were born or even yet conceived. * Clearly He revealed unto * the faithful godly Emperor * that you were an invincible defender of the Church. * And so, by canonical confirmation, * you were elevated and consecrated bishop.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode8C13|ode', 'text' : 'Ode viii.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode8C13|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode8C13|melody', 'text' : 'Guiltless were those Servants.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode8C13|text', 'text' : 'By your hand and by your words of wisdom * the faction of very dangerous Ak√≠ndynos * is vanquished and in jeopardy, * O glorious saint Gregory, * Prelate of Thessalonica. Your theological * and thunderous tongue has made that offensive * company completely, even as smoke, to vanish.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode8C1T|ode', 'text' : 'Ode viii.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode8C1T|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode8C1T|melody', 'text' : 'Guiltless were those Servants.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode8C1T|text', 'text' : 'In you did the Word of God, O Virgin, * refashion our mortal nature that was covered with * passions, in His infinite * goodness and benevolence, * entirely renewing it and sanctifying it. * And we, who have been saved through your childbirth, * offer hymns of glory to you throughout the ages.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode9C11|ode', 'text' : 'Ode ix.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode9C11|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode9C11|melody', 'text' : 'All you born on earth.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode9C11|text', 'text' : 'You preserved unstained * that which is according to God's image in yourself * and regained His likeness too. * For you set bravely your intellect to rule * over the carnal passions, and became a mirror of God. * You have thus become the Holy Trinity's * most illustrious dwelling, O Gregory.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode9C12|ode', 'text' : 'Ode ix.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode9C12|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode9C12|melody', 'text' : 'All you born on earth.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode9C12|text', 'text' : 'The pious Emperor * showed you to be a soaring aerobat when you * who were with the Spirit filled, * became his ally in the attack against * the foolish-minded Barlaam, who spoke unjustly of God * in a lofty manner as a maniac, * over whom you were justly victorious.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode9C13|ode', 'text' : 'Ode ix.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode9C13|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode9C13|melody', 'text' : 'All you born on earth.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode9C13|text', 'text' : 'Filled completely with * superior wisdom and effusing Orthodox * dogmas, O illustrious Saint, * unto the world you have radiated light. * For having in your belly once conceived the fear of God, * you gave birth unto the Holy Spirit's words, * by your love for the better philosophy.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode9C1T|ode', 'text' : 'Ode ix.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode9C1T|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode9C1T|melody', 'text' : 'All you born on earth.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Ode9C1T|text', 'text' : 'All with one accord * we the faithful offer you a hymn of gratitude. * For you who gave birth to God * emancipated us from the ancient curse. * And therefore through you all of us enjoy the fruits of divine * blessing and salvation and enlightenment * and great mercy and also eternal joy.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Exaposteilarion1|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 2.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Exaposteilarion1|melody', 'text' : 'On the mountain.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Exaposteilarion1|text', 'text' : 'Rejoice, the holy fathers' boast, * mouth of the theologians! * Rejoice, O wisdom's dwelling place, * tabernacle of stillness! * Rejoice, O greatest of teachers! * Rejoice, O sea of discourse, * instrument of the active life, * summit of contemplation, and one who heals,* illnesses and passions besetting mankind! * Rejoice, the Holy Spirit's shrine, * dead and alive, O Father!'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|ExapTheotokion|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 2.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|ExapTheotokion|melody', 'text' : 'On the mountain.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|ExapTheotokion|text', 'text' : 'All-holy Lady Queen of all, * come to our aid in dangers. * Anticipate adversities. * Be with us in our hour * of need, indeed at the Last Day. * Let not Satan or Hades, * nor yet perdition capture us. * But through your intercession, enable all * to appear not guilty before the fearful * judgment-seat of your Son and God, * O Lady Theotokos.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Lauds1|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Lauds1|melody', 'text' : 'For the celestial orders.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Lauds1|text', 'text' : 'While in the world, you attained to a life of blessedness. * And now you are exulting with the ranks of the blessed * and dwell, O Bishop Gregory, in the land of the meek, being meek yourself. * And you are rich in God's miracle-working grace, * which you grant to those who honor you.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|LaudsSundayVerse1|text', 'text' : 'The mouth of the righteous man distills wisdom. The lips of righteous men understand grace.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Lauds2|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Lauds2|melody', 'text' : 'For the celestial orders.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Lauds2|text', 'text' : 'O blessed father, you cut down the thorns of heresy, * and in their place you planted sacred Orthodox dogmas. * And with your words you watered the seed of the Faith, thus increasing it splendidly. * And as a practical farmer you brought to God * ears of wheat increased a hundredfold.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|LaudsSundayVerse2|text', 'text' : 'Your priests shall clothe themselves in righteousness; Your saints shall greatly rejoice.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Lauds3|mode', 'text' : 'Mode 1.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Lauds3|melody', 'text' : 'For the celestial orders.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|Lauds3|text', 'text' : 'The ranks of angels and mankind marveled, O blessed one, * at the illustrious glory of your life which was blameless. * For as a steadfast athlete by your resolve you distinguished yourself indeed * as an ascetic and hierarch, and of God * a worthy minister and genuine friend.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|LaudsGlory|mode', 'text' : 'Mode pl. 2.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|LaudsGlory|melody', 'text' : 'Idiomelon.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|LaudsGlory|text', 'text' : 'To those walking in the darkness of their sins You have shone as light, O Christ, during the season of self-control. And reveal to us the auspicious day of Your Passion, so that we may cry to You, "Arise, O God, have mercy on us."'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|LaudsTheotokion|mode', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|LaudsTheotokion|melody', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMA|LaudsTheotokion|text', 'text' : 'You are supremely blessed, O Virgin Theotokos. For through Him who from you became incarnate was Hades taken prisoner, and Adam has been summoned back; the curse has been neutralized, and Eve has been liberated; death has been put to death, and we have been brought to life. Therefore extolling we cry out: O Christ our God, You are blessed, for so was Your good pleasure. Glory to You!'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trLI|Kontakion1|mode', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trLI|Kontakion1|melody', 'text' : ''}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trLI|Kontakion1|text', 'text' : 'With one accord, we sing your praises, Father Gregory * who speaks from God, sonorous trumpet of theology, * and divine and sacred organ of holy wisdom. * But as intellect that stands before the Intellect, * unto Him direct our intellect, so unto you * we may cry aloud: Rejoice, O herald of grace.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trLI|TheotokosHymn|mode', 'text' : 'Mode pl. 4.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trLI|TheotokosHymn|text', 'text' : 'In you, O Lady full of grace, rejoices all creation, the orders of Angels and the human race together. O hallowed temple and rational Garden of Paradise, the pride of virgins, from you did God become incarnate, and our God who existed before the ages became a child. For He made your womb a throne for himself, and your body He made wider than the heavens. In you, O Lady full of grace, rejoices all creation. Glory to you.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trLI|MM|CommunionHymn|text', 'text' : 'For media only.'}
{'id_' : 'tr|d036_en_US_dedes|trMegalynarion|text', 'text' : ''}
